			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3515')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=662&FORUM_ID=3&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&Topic_Title=lvl+35%2D39+%2D+Feerrott+%2D+Single+Specter"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> There is a single specter in the SW corner of Feerrott</P><P>Details:<BR>Spawn time: 5 minutes<BR>Mob Level: 33-37<BR>Problems: Resists... Adds from Skeletons and Bears while siting</P><P>Tactics, modified version I was taught by Ralazar:</P><P>Pull with Darkness from the top of the hill.<BR>Backup to edge of hill<BR>Send pet when you see the specter top the hill.<BR>Fear (undead fear, can't remember name, lvl 29)<BR>Shackel of Bone (don't use this later in levels)<BR>Eterneties Torment (undead DoT, new is SoL)<BR>Venom of Snake<BR>Call back pet.  This is so he doesn't out damage you.  I also don't give him weapons in my later levels.<BR>Sit down<BR>When fear runs out you can either Drain life, and mob will probably try to run, or fear again. I drain if getting low on health, I fear if the mob is higher level.<BR>Send pet back in when mob gets to 40% or so.</P><P>Start timer for 5 minutes. </P><P>Watch for spec trains coming from the cave down the hill, and some of the mobs have very high resists.  If darkness doesn't stick, I just fear and send pet.  the mob runs toward the cave entrance, but will turn around when hit by pet.  He then runs right past me so I can get a darkness off.</P><P>-DV</P><P></P><P> </font></td>

