        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I have something to add.</P><P>You shouldn't really worry about your level 34 pet out damaging you at this level. VoS, the Undead only Dot, Darkness and Boil Blood will serious out damage this sucker. (Vamp. Curse if you are using Call of Bones and are worried about mana0.</P><P>Now what I have found is this...</P><P>We have some pretty decent Undead Only Nukes... the problem is they are Evocation and we don't always use this skill, so for a lot of Necros (minus the ones that spend countless hours nuking poor Jartik to death) will have rather low evocation ability.</P><P>Now Verant in all there infinite wisdom decided to at 44 forget that our past two (any target) nukes were Conjuration and give us a wonderful 495ish dmg fire based nuke. </P><P>Now combine that with your awful evocation skill and what do you have? A hell of a lot of fizzles... so to forgo all this terrible stuff...</P><P>While wasting the Spectre hit him a few times with Ward Undead (the extra damage doesn't hurt) the spell hardly burns mana and your evocation will be going up while you do something constructive.</P><P>I wish I had just done this earlier so my evocation would be a bit higher, I still fizzle a bit when trying to finish something off with Ignite (or rather the Velious non-illusion drop nuke) THANKS VI! *sigh*</P><P>Daevrikk Darkheart<BR>Dark Elven Necromancer <BR>45th Level<BR>Lanys T'vyl Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
