        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Don't count on the level 34 pet being much of a tank.</P><P>When considering Necro pets think of them like a support melee class (ranger,bard,rogue) etc. They change pump out the damage, but they don't have as many hp as say a Magician pet...</P><P>Things i've noticed.</P><P>I've played a Magician for 46 Levels and a Necro for 48, though my sig still says 45 LOL... anyway... we'll for the sake of argument compare them to level 44 pets</P><P>Earth pet<BR>BEAST of a tank<BR>Hits hard, but misses a lot<BR>This guy has less agility then a punching bag, expect him to take hits</P><P>Water pet<BR>Pretty good HP/Agility<BR>Hits harder by +2 dmg then Earth pet, doesn't miss much<BR>Though he hits faster and slightly harder (i think) he has less hp</P><P>Necro pet<BR>Decent hp/good Agility<BR>Hits faster then Earth/Water pet, or atleast hits more often<BR>Hits for +1 more then Earth pet, and -1 then Water pet<BR>Has pretty close hp to the Water pet but has no AC.</P><P>...</P><P>I don't even have a point, besides typing this for the sake of doing something besides sleeping...</P><P>Our pet can tank, but best not to let the situation fall to it. Darkness, Fear, and dot away.  Good old Jober will tear apart oyur foe...</P><P>A Hill Giant is feared<BR>Jober hits a Hill Giant for 47 points of damage<BR>Jober hits a Hill Giant for 47 points of damage<BR>Jober hits a Hill Giant for 47 points of damage<BR>Jober hits a Hill Giant for 47 points of damage<BR>Jober kicks a Hill Giant for 24 points of damage<BR>Jober Staggers<BR>Jober hits a Hill Giant for 47 points of damage<BR>Jober hits a Hill Giant for 47 points of damage<BR>Jober hits a Hill Giant for 47 points of damage<BR>Jober hits a Hill Giant for 47 points of damage<BR>Jober has slain a Hill Giant!</P><P>or...</P><P>A Hill Giant hits Jober for 92 points of damage<BR>A Hill Giant hits Jober for 92 points of damage<BR>A Hill Giant hits Jober for 92 points of 